AB  - The proceedings contain 20 papers. The topics discussed include: development of measurement and calibration techniques for dynamic pressures and temperatures – results and achievements; recent developments of dynamic pressure measurements in combustion engines; low frequency acoustic pressure measurements based on a Fabry Perot refractometer; experimental study of piston rotation rate effect; a parametric methodology for the assignment of pressure values versus refractive measurement; an interactive application for comparison of fit approaches in balances pressure calibration; in-situ liquid density measurement for liquid column manometry; design and development of membrane pressure regulator for cryogenic applications; ‘quantum-based realizations of the pascal’: status and progress of the EMPIR-project: quantumpascal; and circular comparison of conventional pressure standards using a transportable optical refractometer: preparation and transportation.
