AB  - Due to fast development of information technologies, shortened product life-cycles, increasing speed of changing market demands and their processes, digitalization of company processes, the decision makers deal with strategic (and operational) uncertainties more intensively and use failure prevention and safety approaches as well as chaotic trial and error philosophy in their daily tasks. These hyper-complex decision situations request advanced approaches to handle the bounded instability and dichotomy of the parallel-processing of cognitive rational analysis of situations and the intuitive evaluation of dynamical element of development direction. The author will provide the results of a study focusing on management of flexibility as a solution to measure and manage all aspect of an organisational system so that needed adoptions could be done fast and with minimal efforts. The purpose of this study was twofold. The first target was analysing the implementation of the complex management variable flexibility to advanced modelling approaches based on Quantum-Decision-Theory solutions, on screenplay-based modelling set-up and on complementary multi methods handling in cybernetic management modelling. The second aim was as consequences of the implementation to identify the impact on changing toolbox and mind-set, especially with considering digitised modelling of decision making in production logistic assignments. © 2021, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
