AB  - Two-dimensional 1H-31P heteronuclear correlation NMR of trimethylphosphine oxide (TMPO) adsorbed in zeolites, in tandem with DFT calculations, challenges previous one-dimensional 31P NMR assignments, enabling the unambiguous discrimination of Brønsted and Lewis acid sites, extending the understanding of TMPO:Brønsted complexes formed with distinct stoichiometries at the HZSM-5 zeolite surface, and the proton-transfer mechanism. This journal is © The Royal Society of Chemistry.
