AB  - The proceedings contain 497 papers. The topics discussed include: fiber-based sources of quantum light for quantum information processing; spatiotemporal sculpturing of ultrashort pulses; spatiotemporal sculpturing of ultrashort pulses; role of the acousto-optic coupling in a step-index large effective-area fiber with intramodal brillouin scattering; planning security-aware filterless optical networks; resource allocation in quantum-key-distribution-secured datacenter networks with cloud-edge collaboration; time-window based key provisioning in measurement-device-independent quantum key distribution secured optical access networks; multi-hop-based routing and time-slot assignment in centralized quantum entanglement distribution networks; multimodal tissue imaging supported by optical clearing; and deep filtered back projection for photoacoustic image reconstruction.
