VL  - 28
IS  - VOLUME 2
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-84905403101&partnerID=40&md5=9513f25fcf34dbbeba20e3adf04e568f
AB  - The proceedings contain 68 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Advanced Computing, Networking and Informatics. The topics include: Parallel processing concept based vehicular bridge traffic problem; analysis of GPS based vehicle trajectory data for road traffic congestion learning; fast estimation of coverage area in a pervasive computing environment; a fault tolerance approach for mobile agents; path discovery for sinks mobility in obstacle resisting WSNs; blackhole attack defending trusted on-demand routing in ad-hoc network; level wise initial energy assignment in wireless sensor network for better network lifetime; tree based group key agreement - a survey for cognitive radio mobile ad hoc networks; performance analysis of interference aware power control scheme for TDMA in wireless sensor networks; cluster based controlling of route exploring packets in ad-hoc networks; random backoff sleep protocol for energy efficient coverage in wireless sensor networks; distributed diagnosis of permanent and intermittent faults in wireless sensor networks; efficient coverage protocol for homogeneous wireless sensor networks; a novel ICI self-cancellation scheme for improving the performance of OFDM system; design issues and user experience challenges; building a robust software based router; a global routing optimization scheme based on ABC algorithm; AODV routing protocol performance in malicious environment; a probabilistic essential visual cryptographic scheme for plural secret images; the attack back mechanism; privacy preservation of time series data using discrete wavelet transforms; exploring security theory approach in BYOD environment; a framework for analysing the security of chrome extensions; perspective based variable key encryption in LSB steganography; a novel un-compressed video watermarking in wavelet domain using fuzzy inference system; cryptanalysis and security enhancement of two advanced authentication protocols; an efficient RC4 based secure content sniffing for web browsers supporting text and image files; a pairing free certificateless group key agreement protocol with constant round; enhancing the security levels in WLAN via novel IBSPS; varying password based scheme for user authentication; DCT based robust multi-bit steganographic algorithm; service adaptive broking mechanism using MROSP algorithm; performance comparison of hypervisors in the private cloud; an ant colony based load balancing strategy in cloud computing; a demand based resource provisioner for cloud infrastructure; large scale cloud for biometric identification; implementation of symmetric functions using quantum dot cellular automata; dynamic page replacement at the cache memory for the video on demand server; hybrid function based analysis of simple networks; performance augmentation of a FAT filesystem by a hybrid storage system; an approach for compiler optimization to exploit instruction level parallelism; architecting fabricated implant in interconnect for multi-core processor; data concentration on torus embedded hypercube network; SAT based scheduling in high level synthesis; hybrid function based microprocessor realisation of closed loop analysis and synthesis; RFID for indoor position determination; to reduce training cost in EW simulations; detection of communities in social networks using spanning tree; implementation of compressed brute-force pattern search algorithm using VHDL and a modified collaborative filtering approach for collaborating community.
