AB  - The proceedings contain 210 papers. The topics discussed include: wavelength assignment for dynamic traffic in WDM networks; wavelength requirements in wavelength-routed ring networks; fiber-Bragg-grating-based add-drop operation in an amplified multiwavelength multichannel am video transport network; self-healing mechanism in the WDM all optical metropolitan network: SHAONET; implementation of a CMIP-based management interface for optical access network; characteristic of variable-bit-rate video frames duration over the Ethernet network; performance enhancement of ERICA+ using fuzzy logic prediction; performance analysis of an iterative CAC algorithm of stepped link capacity for ATM networks; improved QoS performance bounds for a wireless ATM network; proposal of a data transfer protocol suitable for multimedia communications on shared-media LAN; design and implementation of an expandable ATM interfacing and switching card; remote fiber test system with network element database and geographic information system; an agent-based solution to protection of third party in UPT system; design of electronic commerce workflow model adapted to restructuring value chain for trading costs saving; the design and implementation of an software based on the telecommunication software architecture; theoretic and numerical analysis of nonlinear optical loop mirrors compressing optical pulses; improved wavelength trimming of distributed-feedback lasers using very narrow multiple quantum wells; and high reliability hybrid planer lightwave circuit module integrated with a preamplifier using a plastic package for optical access networks.
