AB  - The growth of a highly crystalline, size selected Si crystals in the size range 1.8-10 nm is presented. These nanocrystals retain bulk-like optical absorption and an indirect band gap down to the smallest size produced. The various electronic transitions are blueshifted by different amounts of quantum confinement. Room temperature photoluminescence (PL) from these nanocrystals was observed in the range 700-350 nm, across the visible range. The most intense PL for the smallest crystals was in blue region of the spectrum and is attributed to direct electron-hole recombination at Γ. The short radiative lifetime for this PL is consistent with this assignment.
