AB  - Calculations for the vibrational excitation of ammonia clusters in collisions with helium atoms were shown. As such, the cluster size distribution was measured with the help of a newly established method. This gives, especially for smaller cluster sizes, more reliable, nearly fragmentation-free results. This new method led to a new assignment of the lowest size distribution of the published results.
